00:14:25,664 --> 00:14:26,722
Yeah. Whatever you want.

257
00:14:26,799 --> 00:14:30,257
I couldn't give the okay to a school
without checking out the grub first.

258
00:14:30,369 --> 00:14:33,270
A girl after my own heart. Tag if you want.

259
00:14:36,609 --> 00:14:37,871
Cool.

260
00:14:38,944 --> 00:14:41,037
So where you from, anyway?

261
00:14:41,914 --> 00:14:43,245
Does it matter?

262
00:14:43,315 --> 00:14:45,442
Not to me, but to some.

263
00:14:46,685 --> 00:14:48,482
Most of us pay to go here.

264
00:14:48,554 --> 00:14:51,045
Some of the other kids,
they're here on scholarship...

265
00:14:51,123 --> 00:14:53,717
so they actually have to
work their way through.

266
00:14:53,792 --> 00:14:55,191
What's the big deal?

267
00:14:55,261 --> 00:14:59,527
It's stupid, really.
It's like this decades- old thing.

268
00:14:59,698 --> 00:15:01,188
The two sides of the town just don't mix.

269
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:02,927
So it seeps into the school.

270
00:15:02,968 --> 00:15:05,835
We avoid them, they avoid us.

271
00:15:07,273 --> 00:15:10,140
Boy, it's fun to grow up
in the middle of a cliché.

272
00:15:10,809 --> 00:15:12,071
Let me get this for you.

273
00:15:12,144 --> 00:15:15,341
First meal's on me.
I'm just gonna get us a table.

274
00:15:38,504 --> 00:15:39,471
Hey.

275
00:15:39,605 --> 00:15:41,835
- Do you know that girl?
- Who?

276
00:15:41,941 --> 00:15:43,875
The one at the register.

277
00:15:43,943 --> 00:15:45,001
Not really.

278
00:15:45,110 --> 00:15:48,341
She's on scholarship.
Like I said, oil and water.

279
00:15:51,483 --> 00:15:53,348
<i>It's</i> Romeo and Juliet.

280
00:15:53,452 --> 00:15:55,215
<i>Kinda. Two worIds. </i>

281
00:15:55,487 --> 00:15:57,318
He's rich, she's poor.

282
00:15:57,389 --> 00:15:59,448
Things wouldn't be kosher
if they were dating.

283
00:15:59,591 --> 00:16:01,889
Are they?
<i>Neither of them are fessing up. </i>

284
00:16:02,161 --> 00:16:04,152
And he's got a very public girlfriend.

285
00:16:04,697 --> 00:16:06,187
This is kinda cool.

286
00:16:06,265 --> 00:16:07,664
We're like a team.

287
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:09,089
A team?

288
00:16:09,468 --> 00:16:13,700
Yeah, like the Wonder Twins,
except we're not twins...

289
00:16:14,006 --> 00:16:15,564
I don't have any super powers.

290
00:16:16,241 --> 00:16:18,038
Yeah. I should get back.

291
00:16:18,110 --> 00:16:20,704
Romeo's getting me nowhere.
I'll try my luck with Juliet.

292
00:16:21,013 --> 00:16:23,607
Good luck, because you know
how well that turned out.

293
00:16:24,583 --> 00:16:25,675
Yeah.

294
00:16:37,463 --> 00:16:39,829
I was wondering
if you could help me. I'm lost.

295
00:16:39,898 --> 00:16:41,229
Who isn't?

296
00:16:43,135 --> 00:16:45,000
Not a fan of this place?

297
00:16:45,337 --> 00:16:46,929
Of high school?

298
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:49,432
I see your point.

299
00:16:51,076 --> 00:16:53,567
I saw you in line in the cafeteria.

300
00:16:53,846 --> 00:16:55,279
- Tru.
- Jen.

301
00:16:56,048 --> 00:16:57,276
DeLuca.

302
00:16:57,583 --> 00:16:59,983
I caught your name tag.

303
00:17:00,719 --> 00:17:02,277
Adam was showing me around.

304
00:17:02,354 --> 00:17:04,720
He seems to have a way with the ladies.

305
00:17:05,024 --> 00:17:06,651
Yeah. I wouldn't know.

306
00:17:06,725 --> 00:17:08,454
He's not really my type.

307
00:17:10,262 --> 00:17:12,253
Yeah, not my brother's either.

308
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:17,100
That's one headache I don't need.

309
00:17:18,237 --> 00:17:20,501
Your brother doesn't like Adam?

310
00:17:20,706 --> 00:17:22,867
No. Derek hates everybody.

311
00:17:22,975 --> 00:17:25,671
You ask a lot of questions
for a prospective.

312
00:17:26,779 --> 00:17:28,007
See you.

313
00:17:34,620 --> 00:17:35,917
Who's your new friend?

314
00:17:35,988 --> 00:17:37,512
Shut up and drive.

315
00:17:58,077 --> 00:17:59,066
Morgue.

316
00:17:59,178 --> 00:18:00,509
<i>Run a DMV check for me. </i>

317
00:18:00,779 --> 00:18:03,339
Someone nicked my brother's car
and didn't leave a note.

318
00:18:03,415 --> 00:18:05,144
The guy's name is Derek DeLuca.

319
00:18:05,217 --> 00:18:07,310
The guy who stole your car gave his name?

320
00:18:07,386 --> 00:18:09,149
Look, not a lot of time here.

321
00:18:09,221 --> 00:18:10,210
<i>AII right. </i>

322
00:18:14,026 --> 00:18:16,392
Bingo. Derek DeLuca.

323
00:18:16,462 --> 00:18:19,397
<i>Looks Iike he's got a coupIe</i>
<i>of outstanding speeding tickets. </i>

324
00:18:19,465 --> 00:18:21,865
You wouldn't
happen to have an address?

325
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:35,538
Hey.

326
00:18:36,815 --> 00:18:37,804
Hey.

327
00:18:40,819 --> 00:18:43,014
Aren't you the girl from the school?

328
00:18:43,355 --> 00:18:47,052
I was giving myself a tour around town,
and I saw you in the driveway.

329
00:18:47,126 --> 00:18:48,593
What are you working on?

330
00:18:48,660 --> 00:18:51,026
I'm just tweaking the air mixture.

331
00:18:54,967 --> 00:18:56,525
How come you don't go to Highland?

332
00:18:56,602 --> 00:18:59,002
You've seen
those trust- fund casualties.

333
00:18:59,238 --> 00:19:00,830
Why do I want to hang out with them?

334
00:19:00,939 --> 00:19:04,807
What, you don't like chilling with rich boys
and their expensive rides?

335
00:19:05,978 --> 00:19:07,707
Can't say I'm a fan.

336
00:19:07,779 --> 00:19:10,270
Of expensive rides,
or the boys who drive them?

337
00:19:10,349 --> 00:19:12,442
Like Adam Whitman?

338
00:19:15,020 --> 00:19:16,988
Don't tell me you're a friend of Whitman's.

339
00:19:17,055 --> 00:19:19,182
I'm not a friend of anybody's yet.

340
00:19:19,258 --> 00:19:21,021
But why, what's your issue with him?

341
00:19:21,093 --> 00:19:24,426
His dad runs the glass factory out on 22.

342
00:19:24,596 --> 00:19:27,190
He fired about 300 people last month.

343
00:19:27,432 --> 00:19:29,332
My dad was one of them.

344
00:19:30,102 --> 00:19:32,195
You seen Adam's new ride?

345
00:19:33,372 --> 00:19:36,341
Probably bought it with the savings
from the layoffs.

346
00:19:36,808 --> 00:19:39,675
I think you and I both know
it's not about the car.

347
00:19:42,047 --> 00:19:44,038
It's about the driver.

348
00:19:44,283 --> 00:19:46,012
Guess we'll see tonight.

349
00:19:46,985 --> 00:19:49,419
What do you mean?
I'm racing Adam.

350
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:52,115
You should come see for yourself.

351
00:19:52,191 --> 00:19:53,249
Car race.

352
00:19:54,993 --> 00:19:56,051
Where?

353
00:19:56,128 --> 00:19:58,392
Lakewood Cliff. Two hours.

354
00:20:16,582 --> 00:20:18,516
I've got a where, but not a how.

355
00:20:18,584 --> 00:20:21,747
If it happens at the race,
it'd explain Adam's death but not Jen's.

356
00:20:21,820 --> 00:20:24,288
I don't know how they ended up
in the car together.

357
00:20:24,890 --> 00:20:26,050
Maybe they weren't.

358
00:20:26,758 --> 00:20:29,522
What do you mean?
<i>'Cause it Iooks Iike an accident...</i>

359
00:20:29,595 --> 00:20:31,028
doesn't mean that it is.

360
00:20:31,096 --> 00:20:33,087
You should know, in our business...

361
00:20:33,165 --> 00:20:35,690
<i>things aren't aIways</i>
<i>what they appear to be. </i>

362
00:20:37,436 --> 00:20:38,630
Thanks, Davis.

363
00:20:40,639 --> 00:20:43,039
I've never had anyone help me before.

364
00:20:45,010 --> 00:20:47,035
I've never had anyone to help.

365
00:20:59,791 --> 00:21:02,726
Do you have a booth?
Something quiet? We have work to do.

366
00:21:02,828 --> 00:21:04,762
All right. Right this way.

367
00:21:14,740 --> 00:21:17,208
Lindsay, is that you?

368
00:21:18,377 --> 00:21:19,639
Harrison.

369
00:21:21,046 --> 00:21:22,707
What a surprise.

370
00:21:22,781 --> 00:21:24,908
Tru told me you were gonna be here.

371
00:21:24,983 --> 00:21:28,077
Come here.
It is so great to see you!

372
00:21:28,387 --> 00:21:29,547
It is?

373
00:21:30,989 --> 00:21:33,150
What's up, my man? Harrison Davies.

374
00:21:34,860 --> 00:21:36,657
I'm an old friend of Lindsay's.

375
00:21:36,728 --> 00:21:38,992
You are?
Are you guys eating?

376
00:21:39,164 --> 00:21:42,998
Because I am starving, and they have
this little shrimp thing...

377
00:21:43,068 --> 00:21:44,763
that is just to die for.

378
00:21:47,072 --> 00:21:51,031
So when I finally stopped,
everyone behind me was covered.

379
00:21:51,143 --> 00:21:53,202
I'm talking head to toe.

380
00:21:54,212 --> 00:21:57,477
And everyone was just glaring at me,
like I meant to do it.

381
00:21:59,418 --> 00:22:01,750
So anyway, that's the most I ever puked.

382
00:22:01,953 --> 00:22:03,853
What about you, Greggers?

383
00:22:03,922 --> 00:22:05,389
Excuse me.

384
00:22:09,161 --> 00:22:10,788
What the hell are you doing?

385
00:22:10,862 --> 00:22:14,298
You are deliberately sabotaging drinks
with my boss.

386
00:22:14,366 --> 00:22:17,062
Apparently, I'm doing this
for your own good.

387
00:22:17,235 --> 00:22:19,703
Giving him every reason
to demote me to phones?

388
00:22:19,805 --> 00:22:21,602
No. Preventing it.

389
00:22:21,707 --> 00:22:23,106
At least that's what I'm told.

390
00:22:23,175 --> 00:22:25,234
Not that I know what to believe anymore.

391
00:22:25,344 --> 00:22:27,539
Harrison, I swear to God....

392
00:22:27,612 --> 00:22:30,945
Look, let's just say I have this friend.

393
00:22:31,049 --> 00:22:32,641
Yeah, you got friends?

394
00:22:33,385 --> 00:22:36,013
Okay, more like a friend of a friend.

395
00:22:36,321 --> 00:22:38,881
Anyway, she used to work for Greg
until she found out...

396
00:22:38,957 --> 00:22:42,518
that"after- hour drinks" were a quick way
for him to get into her--

397
00:22:42,594 --> 00:22:44,653
Okay, stop, please.

398
00:22:44,730 --> 00:22:46,755
You're the only one
that would take it there.

399
00:22:46,832 --> 00:22:49,767
Gregory and I are here to work.

400
00:22:51,737 --> 00:22:52,931
Whatever you say.

401
00:22:57,209 --> 00:22:58,836
How much horsepower?

402
00:22:59,378 --> 00:23:03,508
Hitting 425, going for 12 seconds.

403
00:23:03,615 --> 00:23:05,708
108?
You don't have to do this.

404
00:23:05,784 --> 00:23:07,479
It'll be over before you know it.

405
00:23:07,552 --> 00:23:10,578
And then we'll have
the rest of the night for us.

406
00:23:13,158 --> 00:23:14,489
Hey.

407
00:23:15,060 --> 00:23:16,550
Got a minute?

408
00:23:16,628 --> 00:23:18,789
I didn't know
you were gonna be here.

409
00:23:18,864 --> 00:23:20,422
How did you know we were gonna....

410
00:23:20,499 --> 00:23:22,763
You can't do this. This race.

411
00:23:22,968 --> 00:23:25,061
I'll be fine.
No, you won't.

412
00:23:25,203 --> 00:23:28,832
Something's gonna go very wrong.
This thing Derek has against you--

413
00:23:29,174 --> 00:23:31,039
Is that what this is about?

414
00:23:31,777 --> 00:23:34,109
Don't sweat it. I'm way ahead of you.

415
00:23:36,214 --> 00:23:37,306
Yo, Derek.

416
00:23:40,585 --> 00:23:41,677
Ready to go?

417
00:23:41,753 --> 00:23:44,244
Only if I'm riding with insurance.
lnsurance?

418
00:23:44,322 --> 00:23:46,984
Yeah. He takes one of mine,
I take one of his.

419
00:23:47,058 --> 00:23:49,026
<i>Make sure you know</i>
<i>no one's pIaying around. </i>

420
00:23:49,094 --> 00:23:50,755
Fine. I'll take him.

421
00:23:56,435 --> 00:23:57,834
I'll take her.

422
00:24:09,347 --> 00:24:11,747
No, you can't do this. I'm serious.

423
00:24:11,950 --> 00:24:14,077
Just watch. You'll love it.

424
00:24:23,094 --> 00:24:24,425
You look worried.

425
00:24:24,830 --> 00:24:28,357
How should I look when someone I love
is doing something stupid.

426
00:24:28,433 --> 00:24:30,663
I'm sorry, I can't watch this.

427
00:24:46,485 --> 00:24:49,010
You ready for the ride of your life?

428
00:24:49,554 --> 00:24:51,886
Go, Derek. It's your birthday.

429
00:26:02,260 --> 00:26:03,557
Watch out!

430
00:26:04,963 --> 00:26:05,952
What's she doing?

431
00:26:06,031 --> 00:26:07,498
<i>She's crazy! </i>

432
00:26:07,832 --> 00:26:09,732
Come on! You just cut me off!

433
00:26:49,307 --> 00:26:52,003
You jumped out
in the middle of the street.

434
00:26:53,345 --> 00:26:55,006
<i>Are you insane? </i>

435
00:26:55,080 --> 00:26:57,913
There's no way
I was gonna go over the cliff.

436
00:26:57,983 --> 00:27:00,451
Let it go. You're alive, and you won.

437
00:27:00,518 --> 00:27:02,748
I'm happy, you're happy.

438
00:27:04,122 --> 00:27:06,386
Fair enough. Look, have you seen Amy?

439
00:27:06,458 --> 00:27:08,688
I can't believe she just took off like that.

440
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:09,852
Here's a hint:

441
00:27:09,928 --> 00:27:13,591
Girls in the movies like guys for their cars.

442
00:27:13,999 --> 00:27:16,832
But girls in real life like guys
for who they are.

443
00:27:20,105 --> 00:27:21,595
Thank you.

444
00:27:23,208 --> 00:27:25,506
Hey, where you going?

445
00:27:25,610 --> 00:27:27,271
Back to real life.

446
00:27:36,488 --> 00:27:38,888
Hey. What are you doing right now?

447
00:27:44,095 --> 00:27:46,222
So, nice work. The table.

448
00:27:46,297 --> 00:27:48,458
I usually get stuck by the kitchen.

449
00:27:48,533 --> 00:27:50,160
Yeah, I do what I can.

450
00:27:50,235 --> 00:27:52,601
Since our time always gets cut short...

451
00:27:52,704 --> 00:27:54,194
I want to skip all the work talk...

452
00:27:54,305 --> 00:27:56,933
and move right to anything
other than work.

453
00:27:57,042 --> 00:27:59,875
Good call. But first, no interruptions.

454
00:27:59,944 --> 00:28:00,842
Okay.

455
00:28:02,380 --> 00:28:04,280
All right, I'll start.

456
00:28:04,616 --> 00:28:06,106
What sport did you play growing up?

457
00:28:06,184 --> 00:28:08,345
- Track. You?
- Baseball.

458
00:28:08,853 --> 00:28:10,218
Red Vines or Twizzlers?

459
00:28:10,288 --> 00:28:12,085
Twizzlers, of course.

460
00:28:13,091 --> 00:28:15,252
I'm strictly a Red Vines guy.

461
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:16,657
It's hopeless.

462
00:28:16,728 --> 00:28:19,162
Tragic. I'm dating a Red Vines guy.

463
00:28:21,032 --> 00:28:23,125
My turn. First kiss?

464
00:28:23,735 --> 00:28:25,965
Mandy Banks. Fifth grade.

465
00:28:26,504 --> 00:28:28,734
Worst gift you ever gave a girl?

466
00:28:28,873 --> 00:28:32,070
To Adrian O'Malley when I was 13.

467
00:28:32,143 --> 00:28:35,840
I didn't realize that a gold necklace
should cost more than $3. 95.

468
00:28:38,550 --> 00:28:39,642
Necklace.

469
00:28:39,718 --> 00:28:41,310
You see that necklace?

470
00:28:42,253 --> 00:28:43,311
She wasn't wearing it.

471
00:28:43,388 --> 00:28:46,016
Not after it turned
her entire neck green, no.

472
00:28:49,961 --> 00:28:53,556
This isn't gonna make any sense at all,
but I have to go.

473
00:28:53,832 --> 00:28:54,924
Are you okay?

474
00:28:54,999 --> 00:28:57,126
No. Really, I'm insane...

475
00:28:57,202 --> 00:28:59,966
because I'm about to walk out
on a date that's working.

476
00:29:00,004 --> 00:29:02,768
But it's just
there's somewhere I have to be.

477
00:29:03,241 --> 00:29:04,708
Right now?

478
00:29:04,809 --> 00:29:06,743
There are times when I do this.

479
00:29:06,811 --> 00:29:10,110
Take off. I really wish I could explain why...

480
00:29:10,181 --> 00:29:13,912
but I guess I'm just not
your average 22- year- old girl.

481
00:29:15,253 --> 00:29:17,414
Whether you believe me or not,
I'll call you...

482
00:29:17,489 --> 00:29:20,617
and if you're willing
to give it another try, that's great.

483
00:29:20,692 --> 00:29:23,456
If not, I'll understand.

484
00:29:24,028 --> 00:29:25,188
No, I won't.

485
00:29:25,263 --> 00:29:28,232
I'll be completely crushed, but I'll get it.

486
00:29:30,235 --> 00:29:32,726
Thanks. Really, I had a good time.

487
00:29:46,084 --> 00:29:47,517
Yeah, right.

488
00:29:47,585 --> 00:29:49,212
Where's Adam?
He's around somewhere.

489
00:29:49,287 --> 00:29:49,616
Where's Adam?
He's around somewhere.

490
00:29:49,687 --> 00:29:50,949
What about Jen?

491
00:29:51,022 --> 00:29:53,388
I saw her over there a few minutes ago.

492
00:30:30,662 --> 00:30:32,687
What the hell is going on?

493
00:30:47,312 --> 00:30:48,279
Amy.

494
00:30:51,216 --> 00:30:53,980
- What are you....
- Adam, I'm so sorry.

495
00:30:58,389 --> 00:31:01,324
I knew things weren't great between us,
but how could you--

496
00:31:01,426 --> 00:31:03,758
- Adam, why don't--
- Okay, shut up.

497
00:31:06,030 --> 00:31:07,827
I wanted to tell you.

498
00:31:10,034 --> 00:31:12,161
I didn't know how.

499
00:31:13,538 --> 00:31:15,699
Looks like you figured it out, huh?

500
00:31:31,589 --> 00:31:32,851
I'm so sorry.

501
00:31:35,460 --> 00:31:37,121
For what?

502
00:31:38,930 --> 00:31:40,727
They're all gonna know.

503
00:31:41,199 --> 00:31:43,064
Everyone's gonna know.

504
00:31:43,268 --> 00:31:45,236
Then we'll deal with it.

505
00:31:48,873 --> 00:31:52,036
Remember what we always said
we'd do if people found out?

506
00:31:57,248 --> 00:31:58,647
I don't know.

507
00:31:59,050 --> 00:32:01,177
I've lived here my whole life.

508
00:32:02,120 --> 00:32:05,180
I mean, it's messed up, but it's home.

509
00:32:05,556 --> 00:32:07,251
How they'll look at us?

510
00:32:10,561 --> 00:32:12,290
It won't work here.

511
00:32:13,431 --> 00:32:15,331
We won't work here.

512
00:32:17,969 --> 00:32:20,028
We have to leave, Jen.

513
00:32:22,307 --> 00:32:23,740
Please.

514
00:32:32,884 --> 00:32:35,182
All right. Go home and pack.

