00:32:35,753 --> 00:32:37,846
I'll pick you up in half an hour.

516
00:32:38,923 --> 00:32:40,948
Everything is gonna be fine.

517
00:32:48,533 --> 00:32:50,899
Remember how I said
this was <i>Romeo and JuIiet? </i>

518
00:32:50,969 --> 00:32:54,370
I was wrong. It's Juliet and Juliet.

519
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:56,664
Are you joking?

520
00:32:56,741 --> 00:32:58,732
No. Amy and Jen.

521
00:32:59,310 --> 00:33:00,538
They're the ones in love.

522
00:33:00,645 --> 00:33:02,306
<i>They didn't die during the race. </i>

523
00:33:02,413 --> 00:33:04,881
I don't know what's gonna happen, but....

524
00:33:08,720 --> 00:33:10,187
- Hello?
- I gotta go.

525
00:33:11,055 --> 00:33:12,044
Tru.

526
00:33:17,495 --> 00:33:18,553
Okay.

527
00:33:18,730 --> 00:33:20,391
My round. Lindsay?

528
00:33:21,099 --> 00:33:22,794
Greggers, my man?

529
00:33:24,202 --> 00:33:25,294
No, thanks.

530
00:33:25,370 --> 00:33:27,861
Fine. Keep my seat warm.

531
00:33:34,112 --> 00:33:38,173
I am so sorry.
This is not what I wanted for tonight.

532
00:33:38,549 --> 00:33:39,982
Neither did I.

533
00:33:40,051 --> 00:33:41,609
We have a few minutes.

534
00:33:41,686 --> 00:33:44,450
I could at least go through
some of the proposals that I--

535
00:33:44,522 --> 00:33:47,548
If we've only got a few minutes...

536
00:33:47,625 --> 00:33:50,025
then let's not waste it on work.

537
00:33:55,500 --> 00:33:57,400
He was right?

538
00:33:58,436 --> 00:34:01,633
You should--
You should call it a night.

539
00:34:02,073 --> 00:34:03,335
It's getting late.

540
00:34:03,408 --> 00:34:05,399
You're an important guy.

541
00:34:05,510 --> 00:34:08,411
You want to be fresh
for those morning meetings.

542
00:34:09,814 --> 00:34:11,475
You're probably right.

543
00:34:12,283 --> 00:34:13,682
See you tomorrow.

544
00:34:13,751 --> 00:34:14,979
Gregory.

545
00:34:15,219 --> 00:34:17,312
Don't forget this.

546
00:34:17,989 --> 00:34:20,457
<i>We can discuss it tomorrow at the office? </i>

547
00:34:20,758 --> 00:34:22,316
Right.

548
00:34:22,460 --> 00:34:23,791
Good night.

549
00:34:27,799 --> 00:34:30,495
Wow. This is a first.

550
00:34:32,036 --> 00:34:33,731
Thanks, Harrison.

551
00:34:43,081 --> 00:34:44,048
Hello?

552
00:34:44,382 --> 00:34:45,406
Are you ready?

553
00:34:45,716 --> 00:34:46,944
Yeah, I'm ready.

554
00:34:47,285 --> 00:34:48,582
<i>I know we have to do this. </i>

555
00:34:48,653 --> 00:34:50,245
I love you.

556
00:34:50,321 --> 00:34:51,788
I love you, too.

557
00:34:51,856 --> 00:34:54,324
<i>I'II be there in a few. </i>
<i>Meet me out front. </i>

558
00:34:56,661 --> 00:34:58,652
What are you doing?

559
00:34:58,729 --> 00:35:00,253
Who were you talking to?

560
00:35:00,364 --> 00:35:01,729
Nobody.

561
00:35:01,766 --> 00:35:03,893
No? You said,"I love you."

562
00:35:03,968 --> 00:35:05,731
It's none of your business.

563
00:35:08,372 --> 00:35:10,306
Where are you going?
Get out!

564
00:35:11,409 --> 00:35:14,105
It's Adam. I knew when he
picked you there was something.

565
00:35:14,212 --> 00:35:16,043
You have no idea
what you're talking about!

566
00:35:16,114 --> 00:35:18,309
He picked me because I'm your sister.

567
00:35:20,618 --> 00:35:22,745
Just tell me where you're going.

568
00:35:23,488 --> 00:35:24,819
Out of my way!

569
00:35:43,441 --> 00:35:44,806
What are you doing here?

570
00:35:44,909 --> 00:35:47,173
- Please, just, can you get in?
- No way.

571
00:35:47,278 --> 00:35:50,008
Come on, Jen, just get in.
I've chilled. Seriously.

572
00:35:50,081 --> 00:35:52,311
I just want to talk to you.

573
00:35:52,717 --> 00:35:54,150
About what?

574
00:35:54,252 --> 00:35:56,083
Look, I can't find Amy.

575
00:35:56,154 --> 00:35:58,281
<i>So the Ieast you can do</i>
<i>is give me a minute. </i>

576
00:35:58,356 --> 00:36:00,381
You owe me that.

577
00:36:00,491 --> 00:36:02,015
One minute.

578
00:36:08,266 --> 00:36:09,597
Exactly!

579
00:36:14,338 --> 00:36:17,171
Damn it, Harrison!
Change your oil once in a while!

580
00:36:24,182 --> 00:36:25,149
Derek.

581
00:36:25,750 --> 00:36:27,081
Babe, I'm kinda busy!

582
00:36:27,151 --> 00:36:28,914
I know it's none of my business...

583
00:36:28,986 --> 00:36:31,352
but your sister's with Adam,
and we gotta stop them.

584
00:36:31,422 --> 00:36:33,390
You read my mind. Hop in.

585
00:36:37,361 --> 00:36:41,354
He's upset. And with the way he drives,
I think something might happen.

586
00:36:48,339 --> 00:36:51,069
You said you wanted to talk.
You don't have to drive fast.

587
00:36:51,175 --> 00:36:53,336
How long has this been going on?

588
00:36:54,345 --> 00:36:56,905
- A few months.
- A few months?

589
00:36:59,617 --> 00:37:01,881
I wanted her to tell you.
No.

590
00:37:10,494 --> 00:37:12,826
I can't believe he thinks
he can bag my sister.

591
00:37:12,897 --> 00:37:14,159
She's not sleeping with him.

592
00:37:14,232 --> 00:37:17,099
What do you think they're doing?
Playing Candyland?

593
00:37:18,603 --> 00:37:21,037
Adam, can you slow down?

594
00:37:22,273 --> 00:37:23,831
I'd just like a few answers.

595
00:37:23,908 --> 00:37:26,468
I got in the car
because you need to know something.

596
00:37:26,577 --> 00:37:27,805
Talk fast.

597
00:37:30,081 --> 00:37:32,481
It's not your fault.

598
00:37:32,550 --> 00:37:34,677
<i>ReaIIy, Adam. </i>

599
00:37:34,752 --> 00:37:36,777
<i>She didn't know how to teII you. </i>

600
00:37:37,755 --> 00:37:39,347
She loves you.

601
00:37:43,127 --> 00:37:45,061
But she's in love with you.

602
00:38:01,712 --> 00:38:03,236
The necklace.

603
00:38:04,382 --> 00:38:05,610
I was gonna get it for her.

604
00:38:05,683 --> 00:38:09,278
She was looking at it in the window
of this jewelry store forever.

605
00:38:10,021 --> 00:38:11,318
<i>Now I know why. </i>

606
00:38:11,389 --> 00:38:13,914
She wanted to give it to you.

607
00:38:14,125 --> 00:38:16,753
You're her best friend, Adam.

608
00:38:16,827 --> 00:38:18,556
<i>That's why it was so hard. </i>

609
00:38:18,863 --> 00:38:20,990
She didn't want to hurt you.

610
00:38:28,239 --> 00:38:30,230
Thinking he's all hard, huh?

611
00:38:30,775 --> 00:38:31,833
What are you doing?

612
00:38:31,942 --> 00:38:33,773
Trying to tap my sister in daddy's car?

613
00:38:33,878 --> 00:38:37,439
You gotta get out of the car.
I can't! It won't. The door's jammed.

614
00:38:37,548 --> 00:38:40,847
Your sister's in that car! Stop it!
Just shut up!

615
00:38:41,052 --> 00:38:42,212
You're gonna kill her!

616
00:38:42,286 --> 00:38:45,414
I'm not gonna hurt my sister.
She needs a little scare.

617
00:38:46,724 --> 00:38:48,055
Stop, you'll push them over!

618
00:38:48,125 --> 00:38:50,093
There's a guardrail. I'm just bumping them.

619
00:38:50,161 --> 00:38:51,253
It won't hold.

620
00:38:51,329 --> 00:38:52,591
The guardrail gave way.

621
00:38:52,663 --> 00:38:54,153
Stop! It won't hold!

622
00:38:57,034 --> 00:38:58,365
Poor little rich boy!

623
00:38:58,436 --> 00:39:00,529
Derek, your sister's not in love with Adam.

624
00:39:00,638 --> 00:39:03,368
She's in love with Amy.

625
00:39:06,344 --> 00:39:08,539
That's who she's running away with.

626
00:39:10,548 --> 00:39:11,674
What?

627
00:39:32,703 --> 00:39:34,193
I saw Derek's car.

628
00:40:03,434 --> 00:40:06,335
So you're saying that at exactly this time...

629
00:40:06,537 --> 00:40:09,973
you were with those two dead kids
at the crash site?

630
00:40:10,040 --> 00:40:11,701
That's what I'm saying.

631
00:40:12,877 --> 00:40:15,038
So the girls aren't running away?

632
00:40:15,780 --> 00:40:19,511
No. But it's not like it's all wrapped
up in a neat little bow.

633
00:40:20,184 --> 00:40:23,779
They've still gotta deal with life
now that their little secret is out.

634
00:40:23,854 --> 00:40:26,755
If it weren't for you,
they wouldn't even have that.

635
00:40:27,458 --> 00:40:29,255
If it weren't for us.

636
00:40:31,996 --> 00:40:36,160
Sometimes just being able to talk
to someone can make it a lot easier.

637
00:40:39,069 --> 00:40:40,559
Who are those for?

638
00:40:40,638 --> 00:40:42,902
Amy and Jen gave them to me...

639
00:40:42,973 --> 00:40:45,373
for helping them deal with their secret.

640
00:40:47,745 --> 00:40:50,145
And I'm giving them to you...

641
00:40:51,449 --> 00:40:54,282
for helping me deal with mine.

642
00:41:03,127 --> 00:41:04,219
<i>Yo, Bro. </i>

643
00:41:04,528 --> 00:41:05,586
Tru?

644
00:41:06,697 --> 00:41:07,823
How you doing?

645
00:41:07,898 --> 00:41:08,990
<i>Fine. </i>

646
00:41:09,099 --> 00:41:11,124
Aren't you gonna ask me about your baby?

647
00:41:11,202 --> 00:41:12,533
What baby?

648
00:41:12,603 --> 00:41:13,627
<i>Your car. </i>

649
00:41:13,804 --> 00:41:16,136
Thought that'd be
the first thing out of your mouth.

650
00:41:16,207 --> 00:41:17,231
<i>Yeah, right. </i>

651
00:41:17,341 --> 00:41:20,037
Sorry, I'm just a little busy right now.

652
00:41:20,211 --> 00:41:23,476
Just real quick,
tell me how things went with Lindsay.

653
00:41:23,547 --> 00:41:26,744
Great. No worries. Mission accomplished.

654
00:41:27,685 --> 00:41:28,743
You okay?

655
00:41:28,819 --> 00:41:32,118
Yeah, I'm fine. Look, where are you?

656
00:41:32,189 --> 00:41:33,417
My apartment.

657
00:41:33,591 --> 00:41:35,354
<i>I gotta change to go meet someone. </i>

658
00:41:35,426 --> 00:41:37,587
I don't know if that's the best...

659
00:41:39,530 --> 00:41:41,122
idea.

660
00:41:43,167 --> 00:41:44,896
Oh, my God.

661
00:41:45,603 --> 00:41:46,900
Harrison.

662
00:41:49,440 --> 00:41:53,035
You know, when most girls get up
and run away during the first date...

663
00:41:53,143 --> 00:41:54,337
it's usually a bad sign.

664
00:41:54,445 --> 00:41:55,935
I said I'd call.

665
00:41:56,280 --> 00:41:58,248
Yeah. I thought you meant, like, Tuesday.

666
00:41:58,349 --> 00:42:01,250
Yeah, my timing's been a little off lately.

667
00:42:01,352 --> 00:42:03,252
Can you handle it?

668
00:42:03,654 --> 00:42:05,178
I think I can.

669
00:42:05,623 --> 00:42:09,081
'Cause maybe I'm not looking
for an average 22- year- old.

670
00:42:10,628 --> 00:42:13,995
So you're free all night?
Not going anywhere?

671
00:42:14,798 --> 00:42:16,698
I'm all yours.

672
00:42:20,571 --> 00:42:22,300
You know, a friend of mine was saying...

673
00:42:22,373 --> 00:42:25,206
that real life can't be like the movies...

674
00:42:27,645 --> 00:42:30,705
that maybe sometimes
things are better left to mystery.

675
00:42:33,684 --> 00:42:36,881
What good is a mystery
if you don't try and figure it out?